<h1>Get WhatsApp Group Members</h1>

<p>
    A Chrome extension that lists the members (contacts) of a WhatsApp group.<br>
    Built with <strong>Blazor WebAssembly</strong> and JavaScript interop.
</p>
Inspired by <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oyH3G_ntpKk" target="_blank">this video</a>.

<hr>

<h2>🚀 Features</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Extracts and displays all members of a WhatsApp group directly from WhatsApp Web.</li>
    <li>Clean, Blazor-based popup UI.</li>
    <li>No server or external API required — runs fully client-side.</li>
</ul>

<hr>

<h2>🧰 Requirements</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>.NET 8.0 SDK</strong> (or later)</li>
    <li><strong>Chrome</strong> (or any Chromium-based browser)</li>
</ul>

<hr>

<h2>⚙️ Build</h2>
<p><code>dotnet build</code></p>
<p>This will create the output in the <code>bin/Debug/net9.0/</code> folder.</p>

<hr>

<h2>🦉 Install in Chrome</h2>
<ol>
    <li>Open Chrome and go to: <code>chrome://extensions/</code></li>
    <li>Enable <strong>Developer mode</strong> (toggle in top right).</li>
    <li>Click <strong>Load unpacked</strong>.</li>
    <li>Select the <code>bin/Debug/net9.0/browserextension/</code> folder (or the corresponding Release build path).</li>
    <li>The extension will appear in your Chrome toolbar.</li>
</ol>

<hr>

<h2>▶️ Usage</h2>
<ol>
    <li>Open WhatsApp Web.</li>
    <li>Log in if necessary.</li>
    <li>Navigate to a group chat.</li>
    <li>Open the extension popup.</li>
    <li>Click the <strong>Get chat members</strong> button.</li>
    <li>The list of group members will be displayed and put on the clipboard.</li>
</ol>

<hr>

<h2>⚠️ Notes</h2>
<ul>
    <li>WhatsApp Web updates its DOM frequently — if the extension stops working, selectors in <code>GetMembers.js</code> may need updating.</li>
    <li>This project is for <strong>recreational purposes</strong> only.</li>
</ul>

<hr>

<h2>🛠️ Tech Stack</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Blazor WebAssembly</li>
    <li>Chrome Extensions API (Manifest V3)</li>
    <li>JavaScript interop</li>
</ul>

